#1 <s>As an introverted creative entrepreneur who values privacy greatly, running a business shouldn't feel so awkward, but sometimes it does. Most online resources and mentors tell you to engage with large (evil) tech companies in an outgoing manner. Advertise here according to the algorithm, share your personality charm. Get verified on that service, stay online 24/7, answer with your own videos, and respond immediately. Video, video, still video.
#2 <s>1/3
#3 <s>For me, this year is a year of transformation.
#4 <s>I don't want to dedicate my money, data, and energy to large tech companies anymore, nor do I want to listen to mentors who only apply one-size-fits-all outgoing solutions to everyone. I am exploring new business models while also working to overcome the long-held belief that success can only be achieved in a certain way.
#5 <s>Fingers crossed for me!
#1 <s>Step one is already taken.
#2 <s>I exited FB, removed all Meta and Pinterest trackers from my website, and deactivated my personal WhatsApp account.
#3 <s>Yesterday, I removed the last external tracker from my website - Google Analytics - and felt great about it.
#4 <s>To better support GDPR, I recently subscribed to a European CRM service and will migrate my business over in the coming weeks.
#5 <s>I transferred my MX records to Proton, now have full SPF, DKIM, and DMARC without having to pay Google for basic email validation.
3/3
