Website: You might want to check out @user5. It looks user-friendly and has a nice interface, and it's open-source. I plan to migrate one of my websites over before my next renewal.
Signal: Check out cal.com. It's an open-source calendar service that integrates scheduling for Element, JITSI, and other video calls. It supports Signal, but I haven't tested whether it's just for messaging or video calls as well.
I can recommend @user6. End-to-end encryption, decentralized, open-source.
